{
    "title": "Resizing images uploaded to Amazon S3 with AWS Lambda in Java",
    "description": "Invoke a Java-based AWS Lambda function on Amazon S3 ObjectCreated event to resize an image.",
    "language": "Java",
    "level": "200",
    "framework": "SAM",
    "introBox": {
        "headline": "How it works",
        "text": [
            "This sample project demonstrates how to use a Java-based Lambda function to resize an image from source bucket and put the resized image in a destination bucket.",
            "When a new JPEG image is added to the source S3 bucket, an ObjectCreated event invokes the Java-based Lambda function. The Lambda function retrieves the object from the bucket, resizes it to 800x600 resolution, and then uploads the resized image to the destination bucket.",
            "This pattern uses AWS SAM with Lambda SnapStart on ARM64 architecture on a Java 21 managed runtime."
        ]
    },
